link:labelLink.link:label: Superannuation
Superannuation Account Details Total Value Interest Amount
The amount of superannuation interest that would become payable if the individual voluntarily caused the interest to cease at June 30 of the relevant financial year.
Superannuation Contribution Contribution Amount
The amount of a contribution made by an individual or entity to a superannuation fund.
Superannuation Contribution Defined Benefit Amount
The amount of any defined benefit contributions for a member with a defined benefit interest.
Superannuation Contribution Notice Of Intent Amount
The amount requested, via a notice of intent, which has been accepted by the superannuation fund to be claimed by a member as a personal superannuation contribution deduction.
Superannuation Contribution Notional Taxed Amount
The amount of notional taxed contributions assigned to a defined benefit superannuation fund.
Superannuation Contribution Type Code
A code that represents the type of contribution that is being made by an individual or entity to a superannuation fund.

Valid values are: ESG = Superannuation guarantee - Contribution for the benefit of an employee as mandated by super guarantee legislation AWD = Award or productivity - Contribution for the benefit of an employee as mandated by an award or other industrial agreement SS = Salary sacrifice - Contribution paid on behalf of employees using salary sacrificed earnings VOL = Voluntary - Contribution paid voluntarily on behalf of an employee PER = Personal - Contribution made by an individual to their own account SPS = Spouse - Contribution made by an individual for their spouse's benefit CHD = Child - Contribution made by an individual to the benefit of a person under the age of 18 OTP = Other third party - Contribution made by a third party for the benefit of another person CGR = Capital gains - Small business retirement exemption - Contribution a member has elected to exclude from the non-concessional contributions cap because of a Capital Gains Tax (CGT) small business retirement exemption CGY = Capital gains - Small business 15 year exemption - Contribution a member has elected to exclude from the contributions caps because of a Capital Gains Tax (CGT) small business 15-year exemption PIS = Personal injury election/Structured settlement - Contribution made by a member using personal injury payments or using structured settlement payments RES = Primary residence disposal - Contribution made using proceeds of a primary residence disposal CON = Other concessional contributions - Other concessional transfers to the member's account NON = Other non-concessional contributions - Other non-concessional transfers to the member's account EFF = Excess foreign fund - Transfer from a foreign fund or scheme that exceeded the amount vested in the member at the time of transfer, that is included in the assessable income of the fund NFF = Non-assessable foreign fund - Transfer from a foreign fund or scheme that is not included in the assessable income of the Australian fund AFE = Applicable fund earnings (Elected) - Earnings on a foreign superannuation fund elected by the member NAF = Applicable fund earnings (Not elected) - Earnings on a foreign superannuation fund not elected by the member ATR = Transfers from reserves - Assessable - Transfer an assessable amount to the member's account from a reserve NTR = Transfers from reserves - Non-assessable - Transfer a non-assessable amount to the member's account from a reserve
Superannuation Fund Details Super Choice Exercised Date
The date the employee exercised their choice in super.
Superannuation Fund Details Super Choice Selection Code
A code that specifies what the employee has selected as their option regarding superannuation fund.
Valid Values are: DEF = Use Default AF = Existing APRA Fund NC = Don't want to make a choice right now SMSF = Existing Self Managed Superannuation Fund NE = Not Eligible
Superannuation Payment Transfer Balance Event Amount
The amount of the transfer balance event that applies to the member of a superannuation fund.
Superannuation Payment Transfer Balance Event Code
A code that represents the type of transfer balance event that applies to the member of a superannuation fund.

Valid values are: SIS = Superannuation Income Stream LRB = Limited Recourse Borrowing arrangement IRS = Reversionary Income Stream ICB = Child Death Benefit Income Stream ICR = Reversionary Child Death Benefit Income Stream MCO = Member Commutation CC1 = Commutation Authority - The amount requested has been commuted in full CC2 = Commutation Authority - Unable to commute in full due to insufficient funds CC3 = Commutation Authority - Unable to commute due to the member being deceased CC4 = Commutation Authority - Unable to commute due to a capped defined benefit income stream SSP = Personal Injury (Structured Settlement) STO = Income Stream Stops Being in the Retirement Phase
